President Cyril Ramaphosa says the country will remain on alert level 3 for now. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa says the country will remain on alert level 3 lockdown. The President was briefing the nation following a number of meetings of the Cabinet, the National Coronavirus Command Council (NCCC) and the President's Coordinating Council. He said the NCCC had considered returning all or parts of the country to higher alert levels amid the increasing rate of infections but the economic and social implications would cause greater harm. Ramaphosa said South Africa had 276,242 COVID-19 confirmed cases. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.